<li>J. von Neumann, <i>Mathematical Foundations of Quantum Mechanics</i>, Princeton University Press, 1955. Reprinted in paperback form.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/R._F._Streater" title="R. F. Streater" class="mw-redirect">R. F. Streater</a> and <a href="/wiki/A._S._Wightman" title="A. S. Wightman" class="mw-redirect">A. S. Wightman</a>, <i>PCT, Spin and Statistics and All That</i>, Benjamin 1964 (Reprinted by Princeton University Press)</li>
<li>M. Reed and B. Simon, <i>Methods of Mathematical Physics</i>, vols I-IV, Academic Press 1972.</li>
<li>G. Teschl, <i>Mathematical Methods in Quantum Mechanics with Applications to Schrödinger Operators</i>, <a href="http://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~gerald/ftp/book-schroe/" class="external free" title="http://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~gerald/ftp/book-schroe/" rel="nofollow">http://www.mat.univie.ac.at/~gerald/ftp/book-schroe/</a>, American Mathematical Society, 2009.</li>
<li>N. Weaver, "Mathematical Quantization", Chapman &amp; Hall/CRC 2001.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hermann_Weyl" title="Hermann Weyl">H. Weyl</a>, <i>The Theory of Groups and Quantum Mechanics</i>, Dover Publications, 1950.</li>
</ul>


